Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.64,0:02:54.97,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.75,0:02:57.53,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police and an ambulance, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:05.29,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Was anyone hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.42,0:03:08.12,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.60,0:03:10.74,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:15.88,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.08,0:03:22.53,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like making two students \Nnot exist didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.53,0:03:35.14,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm at my wit's end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.78,0:03:37.23,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm so tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.55,0:03:42.20,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:44.34,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Kubodera...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:48.49,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure you understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.22,0:03:52.74,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.01,0:04:02.47,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That troubled me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.39,0:04:07.74,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.90,0:04:17.27,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the result of an investigation \Nof Mr. Kubodera's home was disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.96,0:04:19.92,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kubodera was a bachelor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.92,0:04:22.35,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,who still lived with his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:25.02,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She was well on in years,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.02,0:04:29.34,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,and had been bedridden for some \Ntime, due to a serious illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.41,0:04:35.03,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,They found her dead in her bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.59,0:04:37.79,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She had clearly been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.28,0:04:41.30,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,The stress of caring for her... \NThe class 3 calamity...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.72,0:04:50.07,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he felt so trapped by it all \Nthat it drove him to kill his own mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.26,0:04:54.30,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,And then he killed himself \Nin front of his students.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.81,0:04:58.94,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he make such extreme decisions?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:02.07,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You think this was a \Nresult of the phenomenon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:03.23,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:08.64,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So he was drawn into death \Nby otherwise unlikely means?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.42,0:05:12.33,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Could there be any other explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.47,0:05:16.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,The calamity hasn't been stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:19.94,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,People will keep dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.92,0:05:22.42,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,There was nothing we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.42,0:05:25.05,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Sakaki, don't get so down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:28.64,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Blaming yourself won't change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.07,0:05:26.57,Default,Tape,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Do Not Enter
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.07,0:05:31.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Until recently, you were...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.30,0:05:34.91,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and it was breaking my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.40,0:05:39.08,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You know the whole story now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.08,0:05:41.16,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,So you get where I'm coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.16,0:05:44.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I understand perfectly well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.35,0:05:47.95,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Misaki? \NFeel like a weight's been lifted?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:50.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.63,0:05:52.62,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't really feel a \Nweight to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.11,0:05:56.04,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You are seriously weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.11,0:06:00.49,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.52,0:06:06.63,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, what's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:08.53,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You both might exist again,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:10.43,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,but you'd best be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.87,0:06:11.80,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:15.31,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:17.43,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:19.81,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,People will say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.58,0:06:23.97,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you'll be \Nconsidered completely innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.97,0:06:27.10,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm sure I'll be accused \Nof incompetence, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:28.32,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.77,0:06:31.65,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:38.45,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't blame Kouichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.45,0:06:40.04,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,no matter what anyone says.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.81,0:06:42.54,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:46.12,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,The calamity, and my work as \Nhead of countermeasures,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.98,0:06:48.54,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,are only just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.99,0:06:52.69,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if anyone will go
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.69,0:06:54.68,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,into hiding now, until summer break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:56.12,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:59.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Some people may have fled town already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:00.48,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.48,0:07:02.92,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It happens every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:04.62,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There are always people who leave
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.62,0:07:06.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yomiyama for summer break.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.09,0:07:08.52,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,It's all so strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.99,0:07:12.44,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,But you really are weird, Misaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.44,0:07:14.53,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You talk like this doesn't involve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:15.33,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Do I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:19.71,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that you're \Nactually the extra this year?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:23.96,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It could very well be you, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:26.88,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me? No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.88,0:07:28.34,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even joke about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.75,0:07:30.26,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There's really no way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.26,0:07:31.53,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.53,0:07:34.74,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I have no memories of dying!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.74,0:07:35.70,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,And, not to brag,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.70,0:07:38.31,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,but I clearly remember all \Nthe shit I got into as a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.22,0:07:58.58,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,You look well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.43,0:08:00.75,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.57,0:08:04.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Was Akazawa here to talk \Nto you about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.78,0:08:06.53,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,As head of countermeasures,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.53,0:08:07.87,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,she comes here often.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.32,0:08:09.66,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.43,0:08:14.46,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She's a strong girl, and she knows that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.03,0:08:17.14,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,but considering what she's up against...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.88,0:08:20.51,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I pity her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.46,0:08:26.18,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Ms. Mikami \Ndropped by today, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.18,0:08:28.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.94,0:08:32.11,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,She knows my history here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.11,0:08:34.56,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,There was something she \Nwanted to formally discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.95,0:08:37.15,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,And what brings you two here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.15,0:08:42.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to ask about 15 years ago, \Nwhen the calamity stopped midyear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.18,0:08:47.68,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That was the one time \Nin the past 25 years
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.68,0:08:49.53,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,when it stopped midyear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:09:04.89,Default,Book,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}April 12, sister, Kyouko, illness \NJuly 23, sister, Ikumi, illness \NJune 6, accident \NJune 13, accident \NAugust 9, accident \NAugust 9, accident
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.58,0:08:58.53,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Excluding Ritsuko, whom I didn't know about,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.53,0:09:00.68,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,there were seven deaths that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:03.06,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,When did Ritsuko die?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.69,0:09:04.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,In July.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.62,0:09:06.55,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:09.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the deaths \Nstopped in August?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.76,0:09:12.66,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and look at the date \Nof the August deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.58,0:09:15.36,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,August 9...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:20.20,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,That class had just left \Nfor a class trip on August 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:21.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Class trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.36,0:09:25.00,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think something may have \Nhappened during summer break...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.00,0:09:27.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So two students died in \Naccidents on that trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:34.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And something happened on that trip \Nthat stopped the calamity?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.29,0:09:35.51,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.81,0:09:38.85,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Notice that no one is listed \Nas "deceased" on that page.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.62,0:09:39.76,Default,Book,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Deceased:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.76,0:09:43.89,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It never became clear who \Nthe dead person was that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.11,0:09:46.46,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Why did it stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:48.24,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:52.81,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But I do know that they \Nvisited the Yomiyama Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:53.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,A shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.30,0:09:59.56,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,A very old shrine, located \Nhalfway up Mt. Yomiyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.56,0:10:02.05,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Their lodge was at\Nthe foot of that mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.05,0:10:04.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe if we visit the shrine...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:06.59,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, people went back to it in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.59,0:10:08.46,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,years when the calamity occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.95,0:10:11.67,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,but it had no effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.63,0:10:15.55,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So the shrine had nothing to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.55,0:10:17.87,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not conclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.42,0:10:22.09,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,It could be that going \Nthere in a large group,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.09,0:10:23.60,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,in early August, was effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.40,0:10:27.80,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, we can't deny the \Npossibility that the effect came
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.80,0:10:30.44,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,from something else, unrelated \Nto visiting the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.44,0:10:35.07,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,This is what Ms. Mikami came \Nhere to discuss with me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:38.15,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}July 17 (Fri.)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.59,0:10:38.15,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,This may seem abrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.15,0:10:40.70,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,but we will be conducting a class trip
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:43.30,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,from August 8-10, for three \Ndays and two nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.21,0:10:47.07,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,Please prioritize this event,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.78,0:10:51.23,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,and plan to participate, \Nif at all possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:53.59,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,You will receive additional \Ndetails in the coming days.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:55.73,Default,Mikami,0000,0000,0000,,I will mail the forms to all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.27,0:10:57.44,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Question!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.73,0:11:02.93,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:17.07,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:21.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:30.62,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.30,0:11:43.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The dead one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.04,0:11:45.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,...is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.41,0:11:48.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.23,0:12:16.08,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Dad
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:19.11,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.11,0:12:21.44,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, India just gets hotter and hotter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.44,0:12:22.78,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,How've you been, kiddo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:25.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:26.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.71,0:12:30.39,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, everyone's doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:35.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.79,0:12:39.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever seen any of Mom's \Nphotos from junior high?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.45,0:12:40.91,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Photos?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:42.48,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure she showed me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:44.66,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,her graduation album when we got engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:46.95,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Any others?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.95,0:12:49.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like, have you seen the group photo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.13,0:12:51.66,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,her class took after their \Ngraduation ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.10,0:12:54.62,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Group photo? Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.86,0:12:57.67,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've heard that it \Nwas kind of weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:04.17,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Do Not Enter
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.13,0:13:01.21,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like, a ghost photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.21,0:13:04.17,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you hear a \Nsilly story like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:06.39,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, ghost photos are just—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.39,0:13:07.93,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.93,0:13:10.87,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, actually, now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.87,0:13:13.24,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,I might've heard a story \Nlike that, a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.82,0:13:16.44,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Something about a creepy photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.03,0:13:18.71,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.71,0:13:19.44,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.77,0:13:21.59,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't like having it near her,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.59,0:13:23.19,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,so she left it at her parents' place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.45,0:13:24.49,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Her parents' place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.11,0:13:28.35,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kouichi, something goin' on there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:30.21,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.21,0:13:32.02,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just kinda bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.02,0:13:33.48,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.47,0:13:38.53,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Ritsuko was \Na very special lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.53,0:13:42.04,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,My feelings for her haven't changed a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.04,0:13:44.31,Default,Yousuke,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why you're my—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.31,0:13:45.38,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:46.78,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.64,0:13:54.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Inoya?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.93,0:13:58.59,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know where that is, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.59,0:13:59.45,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Today?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.22,0:14:02.59,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, dude!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.59,0:14:04.03,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.27,0:14:06.09,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You got a date with Mei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.09,0:14:08.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What is it you want to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.25,0:14:10.95,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotta be in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.95,0:14:12.87,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got a date, \Njust bring Mei along.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.87,0:14:14.79,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,This problem involves \Nthe whole class, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.53,0:14:18.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:22.92,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Kouichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.27,0:14:24.17,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.90,0:14:26.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Akazawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.62,0:14:28.94,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Teshigawara called you here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.94,0:14:30.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.67,0:14:31.83,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.58,0:14:33.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,He called you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:35.12,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:37.68,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Only because he said it \N"involves the whole class."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.68,0:14:41.52,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't go anywhere at \Nhis invitation otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:48.03,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Teshigawara filled me in on \Nwhat happened 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.43,0:14:52.19,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And about your mom, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:53.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.74,0:14:55.87,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:00.62,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,A friend of yours, Izumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.62,0:15:01.70,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.70,0:15:04.15,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,This is my classmate, \NKouichi Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.15,0:15:07.14,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that must make you \NYuuya's friend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:09.17,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for being so kind to my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:12.45,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Yuuya Mochizuki's \Nolder sister, Tomoka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.45,0:15:13.61,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.61,0:15:15.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes, likewise.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.79,0:15:18.80,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Yuuya has told me a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.80,0:15:19.96,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What can I get for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:21.94,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:23.59,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,He'll have the same as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.29,0:15:25.48,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:27.98,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Coming right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.14,0:15:32.81,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What did you get?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.81,0:15:33.98,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.98,0:15:37.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like coffee. It's too bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.25,0:15:38.91,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the coffee here is the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.63,0:15:42.18,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,They use Hawaiian Kona Extra Fancy beans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:44.51,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.51,0:15:45.67,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Please enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.67,0:15:49.27,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Just take my word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.27,0:15:50.84,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:15:59.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's bitter, but also sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.19,0:16:01.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:08.26,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,So, you didn't go back to Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.92,0:16:12.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No. It'd feel like I was \Nrunning away, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.55,0:16:18.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I've started to wonder \Nif it's me who's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:22.00,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you were never born.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:25.69,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe 15 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.69,0:16:29.17,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,the calamity took your mother's life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.17,0:16:32.38,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,and she couldn't give birth to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.73,0:16:34.85,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And now, 15 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.85,0:16:38.46,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,you've come back to life as a \Ntransfer student in class 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:40.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.26,0:16:42.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.12,0:16:48.64,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take me so seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.66,0:16:52.19,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,True, I did consider the possibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.86,0:16:53.89,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.48,0:16:56.62,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Shake my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.93,0:17:05.92,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I still get the feeling \Nthat we've met...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:09.77,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,No, that I've shaken your \Nhand somewhere before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.77,0:17:11.71,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.87,0:17:14.97,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't call up a visual memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.97,0:17:17.76,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,but my hand physically remembers yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.26,0:17:21.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.34,0:17:23.02,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,you shook my hand at the hospital, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:24.91,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do that for a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.56,0:17:29.44,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,There's a rumor that dead people \Nhave shockingly cold hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.64,0:17:32.89,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it's true, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.89,0:17:35.24,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,If it were that easy to tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:37.22,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:39.13,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:42.66,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.33,0:17:47.48,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you do that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.48,0:17:49.40,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Do you hate me that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.80,0:17:51.16,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Want the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:53.30,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.30,0:17:55.45,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, whatever. I'll let it slide today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.90,0:17:59.45,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.45,0:18:02.09,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,You tell them, Mochizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.79,0:18:03.56,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.32,0:18:06.00,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Since there's a chance
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:09.23,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,that my sister could become \Ninvolved in what's going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.23,0:18:11.62,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my sister is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:13.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Tomoka, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.15,0:18:14.18,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.18,0:18:18.20,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I just couldn't \Nkeep quiet about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.46,0:18:19.78,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You told her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.40,0:18:22.22,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Down to the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.22,0:18:25.26,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,She went to Yomi North, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:27.51,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,so she knew the rumors about class 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.51,0:18:32.37,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,And Tomoka actually gave us a \Nsurprising bit of info.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.18,0:18:41.39,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,One of our regulars is a man \Nnamed Katsumi Matsunaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.39,0:18:44.50,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,I knew he went to Yomi North,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:48.06,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,but I recently found out \Nthat he was in class 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.70,0:18:51.47,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,I worked up the courage to ask him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.47,0:18:54.40,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,if {\i1}it{\i0} had happened in his year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:55.35,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,And he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.42,0:18:58.60,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,The curse that year wasn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.23,0:19:01.29,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:03.01,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,I saved them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.92,0:19:05.91,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,I saved them!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:09.54,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,I knew I had to tell them! \NSo that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.04,0:19:11.12,Default,Matsunaga,0000,0000,0000,,I left it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.26,0:19:14.84,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean? Left what, where?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.84,0:19:17.52,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't seem to recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:19.07,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,I've asked him about it many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.07,0:19:21.22,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,but he insists he has no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:22.97,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Makes you curious, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.35,0:19:26.30,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,This Matsunaga guy \Nstopped the calamity?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.76,0:19:29.94,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And he left a hint on how \Nhe did it somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.94,0:19:31.45,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,That's gotta be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.94,0:19:37.19,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,So, I'm thinking we should talk \Nto this Matsunaga guy ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.67,0:19:40.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where we can find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:43.09,Default,Tomoka,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't know where he lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.09,0:19:44.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:49.79,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know someone who \Nwas in Matsunaga's class?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:59.33,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so he was your aunt's classmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.33,0:20:02.94,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If I find out where Matsunaga is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.73,0:20:05.10,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,will you come with me to see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.31,0:20:14.79,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You really were the model \Nfor that doll, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:18.65,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You said only half, \Nbut it looks just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:23.07,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This girl is the daughter she \Ngave birth to 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.89,0:20:25.22,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Your sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.22,0:20:28.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But she was stillborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.79,0:20:33.85,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She made this doll based on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:37.32,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,the daughter who never \Nhad a chance to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.93,0:20:41.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So it's only half me, if not less.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.69,0:20:48.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I have somewhere \Nto be tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.11,0:20:49.46,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.46,0:20:51.29,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,My parents want me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.29,0:20:54.28,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,to go with them to their summer house.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.79,0:20:57.19,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't tell them I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:20:59.36,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is it outside Yomiyama?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.36,0:21:00.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.43,0:21:02.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So you're leaving town?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.82,0:21:06.48,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,We'll only be gone a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.48,0:21:09.32,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back for the class trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.32,0:21:10.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.08,0:21:19.59,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, have you found that ghost picture
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.59,0:21:22.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,your mother left \Nat her parents' house?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.09,0:21:23.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.20,0:21:26.84,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If you find it, will you show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.21,0:21:28.19,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.72,0:21:36.19,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,If anything comes up, use this number.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.17,0:21:40.63,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a phone number?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.23,0:21:42.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,For a cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.12,0:21:43.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.23,0:21:44.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.08,0:21:44.82,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.42,0:21:47.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You said you hated those devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.89,0:21:49.68,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.68,0:21:53.50,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Being connected to people all the time \Nby electromagnetic waves disturbs me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.24,0:21:55.93,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then why do you have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.93,0:21:57.79,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She makes me carry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.79,0:22:01.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She claims to feel uneasy at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.03,0:22:03.21,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.28,0:22:06.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.16,0:22:08.24,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.24,0:22:12.41,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You said you wondered if \Nit's you who's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.41,0:22:13.43,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.43,0:22:14.96,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Has your suspicion been laid to rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.33,0:22:16.27,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.27,0:22:31.36,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.36,0:22:34.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,New dolls are put in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.87,0:22:50.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.84,0:22:52.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.31,0:22:57.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the one who's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.74,0:24:40.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hair stand.
